content.description: Climb up the slab next to a large stump. This is also a down climb.
content.location: Clear-cut Boulder. Refer to Rock Climbing Western Oregon, Vol. 2: Umpqua map pages 66-67, photo and map 13 pages 169-170, map page 72, and page 77.

content.description: Start on left arete of the east face, move out right on good edges without any real good foot holds, lunge for the top and be careful not to blow the top-out.
content.location: East Face of Clear-cut Boulder, Callahans. Refer to Rock Climbing Western Oregon, Vol. 2: Umpqua map pages 66-67, photo and map 13 pages 169-170, map page 72, and page 77.

content.description: This house size boulder lies in the middle of a young stand of trees. Steep 15+foot walls of fine-textured Tyee sandstone provide for challenging boulder problems. This area deserves to be readopted and some TLC.
